The paper proposes a machine learning algorithm for sequential online prediction, which involves modeling temporal structures in streaming data and detecting outliers and change points. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), statistics (cs.ST), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and information theory (cs.IT). Among these, machine learning and artificial intelligence are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the proposed algorithm's development and evaluation. Statistics and data structures and algorithms are also relevant, as they involve modeling and analyzing data, while information theory could be relevant for the algorithm's theoretical analysis.
